In a #small pot{}, combine @white rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups},
and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce
heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until Step 5.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Drain and rinse @corn{1}, then pat very dry with #paper towels{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over high heat.
Add corn, @Fajita Spice Blend{1%tbsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and
@pepper{pinch}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until corn is golden brown
and lightly charred in spots, ~{4-6%minutes}. (TIP: Cover with a lid
if kernels start to pop!) Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{}.
Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, dice @tomato{1}(diced into 1/2-inch pieces). Trim and thinly
slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced). Quarter @lemon{1}(quartered).

Open package of @diced chicken thighs{10%oz} and drain off any excess
liquid. Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for corn over medium-high heat.
Add chicken in a single layer and season with @Mexican Spice Blend{1%tbsp}
and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through,
~{4-6%minutes}.

To bowl with charred corn, add tomato, half the scallions, a drizzle of
@olive oil{1%tsp}, juice from one lemon wedge, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}
and @pepper{pinch}. Stir to combine.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{3%tbsp}, juice from one lemon
wedge, salt, and pepper to taste. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture
reaches a drizzling consistency.

Fluff rice with a fork. Stir in @pepitas{1/2%oz}.

> TIP: If you have extra time, toast pepitas beforehand in a small dry
> skillet over medium heat, stirring frequently, for 1-2 minutes to add
> extra flavor and crunch!

Divide pepita rice between shallow #bowls{}. Using a #slotted spoon{}, top
with salsa (draining first) and chicken in separate sections.

Drizzle with lemon crema and as much @hot sauce{1%tsp} as you like. Top
with remaining scallions and serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.